<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910719-0016</DOCNO><DOCID>910719-0016.</DOCID><HL>   McDonnell Douglas Union Talks</HL><DATE>07/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3</SO><CO>   LABOR MD</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><NS>LABOR, PERSONNEL ISSUES, TRENDS, MANAGEMENT TECHNIQUES (LAB)</NS><RE>MISSOURI (MO)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   LONG BEACH, Calif. -- McDonnell Douglas Corp. saidcontract talks resumed this week between the company and theUnited Auto Workers union.   The negotiations broke off in late April. At that time,officials from the union's international office in Detroitwanted to accept the company's most recent contract offer,but local UAW leaders opposed the proposed pact, and the rankand file overwhelmingly rejected it in a ratification vote.</LP><TEXT>   The most recent UAW contract, covering about 23,000workers, expired in March. But the company is continuing tocover members under the old agreement pending a new accord.</TEXT></DOC>